### Revive Threads Brings Zero-Waste Fashion to Portland's Pearl District

**PORTLAND, OR – [7/7/2024]** – Revive Threads, the online sustainable fashion brand known for turning deadstock fabric into premium streetwear, today announced the opening of its first-ever brick-and-mortar retail space at 1234 NW Lovejoy Street.

The 1,200-square-foot boutique opens its doors on [09/15/2024] and will feature an interactive "repair bar" where customers can learn basic mending techniques—a core tenet of the brand's "Wear it Longer" philosophy.

**"Portland has always been our spiritual home,"** said [Jimmy Tailor], CEO of Revive Threads. *"Our customers here understand that sustainability isn't a trend—it's a responsibility. This store allows us to build a physical community around that mission."*

**The store will feature:**
- Exclusive in-store drops not available online
- Weekly sewing workshops hosted by local textile artists
- A fabric library showcasing salvaged materials used in production

